      "description": "Up for sale is a driver-focused 2002 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six, equipped with individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing. This example delivers linear power delivery up to its 8,000 RPM redline, paired with a tactile 6-speed Getrag manual transmission. The chassis remains composed thanks to a reinforced rear subframe and refreshed trailing arm bushings, mitigating common E46 floor pan fatigue. It retains the factory-spec Variable M Differential Lock for optimal corner-exit traction. While showing minor cosmetic patina consistent with spirited use, the mechanical vitals\u2014including recent valve clearances and rod bearing service\u2014are documented and up to date, ensuring this high-revving M-car performs exactly as Munich intended.",
